## 2. Dataset Description

| | |
|---|---|
| **File** | `data/smart_city_complaints_50k.csv` |
| **Rows** | 50,000 complaints |
| **Columns** | 22 |
| **Time range** | Jan 2023 – Dec 2024 |
| **Zones** | 8 (Central, East, West, North, South, North-East, South-West, Industrial) |
| **Categories** | 7 (Garbage Collection, Water Supply, Road Damage, Street Light Failure, Traffic Congestion, Drainage Problem, Public Safety) |
| **Departments** | 7 (Sanitation, Water Supply, Public Works, Electricity, Drainage, Traffic Management, Police) |

**Key columns:** `Complaint_Date`, `Resolved_Date`, `Zone`, `Category`, `Department`,
`Priority` / `Priority_Score`, `Status`, `Resolution_Delay_Days`, `Citizen_Satisfaction_Score`,
`Complaint_Description`, `Feedback_Comments`.

**Data quality:** No duplicate rows. The only missing values are `Resolved_Date` /
`Resolution_Delay_Days` for the 17,527 complaints still `Pending` or `In Progress` —
this is expected missingness, not bad data (handled via an `Is_Resolved` flag, see notebook).

